apiKey.description: API key for Sonarr authentication. Can be specified via the `SONARR_API_KEY` environment variable.

url.description:
Full Sonarr URL with protocol and port (e.g. `https://test.sonarr.tv:8989`). You should **NOT** supply any path
(`/api`), the SDK will use the appropriate paths. Can be specified via the `SONARR_URL` environment variable.

provider.description:
The provider type for the sonarr package. By default, resources use package-wide configuration
settings, however an explicit `Provider` instance may be created and passed during resource
construction to achieve fine-grained programmatic control over provider settings. See the
[documentation](https://www.pulumi.com/docs/reference/programming-model/#providers) for more information.

sonarr:DownloadClients/downloadClient:Do.description:
<!-- subcategory:Download Clients -->Generic Download Client resource. When possible use a specific resource instead.
For more information refer to [Download Client](https://wiki.servarr.com/sonarr/settings#download-clients).

{{% examples %}}
## Example Usage
{{% example %}}

```typescript
import * as pulumi from "@pulumi/pulumi";
import * as sonarr from "@maienm/pulumi-sonarr";

const example = new sonarr.downloadclients.DownloadClient("example", {
    configContract: "TransmissionSettings",
    enable: true,
    host: "transmission",
    implementation: "Transmission",
    name: "Example",
    port: 9091,
    priority: 1,
    protocol: "torrent",
    urlBase: "/transmission/",
});
```
```python
import pulumi
import pulumi_sonarr as sonarr

example = sonarr.download_clients.DownloadClient("example",
    config_contract="TransmissionSettings",
    enable=True,
    host="transmission",
    implementation="Transmission",
    name="Example",
    port=9091,
    priority=1,
    protocol="torrent",
    url_base="/transmission/")
```

downloadPropersRepacks.description: Download proper and repack policy. valid inputs are: 'preferAndUpgrade', 'doNotUpgrade', and 'doNotPrefer'.

episodeTitleRequired.description: Episode title requirement policy. valid inputs are: 'always', 'bulkSeasonReleases' and 'never'.

extraFileExtensions.description: Comma separated list of extra files to import (.nfo will be imported as .nfo-orig).

fileDate.description: Define the file date modification. valid inputs are: 'none', 'localAirDate, and 'utcAirDate'.

importExtraFiles.description: Import extra files. If enabled it will leverage 'extra*file*extensions'.

minimumFreeSpace.description: Minimum free space in MB to allow import.

				&profiles.QualityProfileQualityGroupArgs{
					Qualities: profiles.QualityProfileQualityGroupQualityArray{
						profiles.GetQualityResult(bluray),

				},

		}
		return nil
	})
}

        final var webdl = ProfilesFunctions.getQuality(GetQualityArgs.builder()
            .name("WEBDL-2160p")
